      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INVINCIBLE RED (5) finished third two runs back at Roma then improved last time out to score by 2.25 lengths over 1400m at Charleville. Darren Evans scored on him last time and retains the ride. Taking on a better line-up this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. ACEDROD (6) finished 4 lengths back in sixth over 1200m at Emerald last time out after a gutsy win the start prior. Goes well at this journey with two wins and two placings from five starts and is one of the chief contenders. MOORABINDA MICK (7) was below his best last time when sixth over 1400m at Ilfracombe, beaten 7 lengths. Likely improver with top-three prospects from the low draw. HURTLE (2) travelled in a rearwards position then picked up fairly well in the straight and finished 2 lengths away in fifth last time out over 1200m at Barcaldine two weeks ago. Steps up in distance today and is a must for the exotics players.",
